      "widgets_values": [
        "QWEN-IMAGE-EDIT 2511 - instruction IMAGE EDITING (local, free)\n\nLoad an image + type an instruction in 'Edit instruction' -> edited image.\nThe surgical editor: precise text/object/color/identity edits.\n\nEXAMPLES:  change the jacket to red  |  remove the person on the left  |\n  change the sign text to 'OPEN 24H'  |  make it night with neon lights  |\n  put this character in a suit (keeps the face)\n\nSETTINGS: steps 20 (raise to 40 for max quality), CFG 4.0, euler/simple.\n  Lower CFG (2.5-3)=gentler edits, higher (4-5)=stronger instruction.\n  This graph uses the official 2511 wiring (ModelSamplingAuraFlow 3.1 +\n  CFGNorm + FluxKontextMultiReferenceLatentMethod) - required, don't remove.\n\nMULTI-IMAGE EDIT: connect more images to image2 / image3 on the encoders\n  (e.g. 'put the hat from image2 on the person in image1').\nHEAVY 20B model: ~60-170s/image on 16GB (offloads to RAM)."
      ],
      "color": "#443322",
      "bgcolor": "#443322"
    }
